<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">They're still there as of this morning.  The normal food and drink vendors sell the holiday food and drink while the general "Merchant" vendors sell the holiday candles as well as the food and drink.
<br />

<br />
There are vendors in every Freeport and Qeynos neighborhood.  My guess is that they'll keep them in until the "big patch" (after New Year's).
<br />

<br />
I've played a lot on Test (one of each archetype in their teens).  Believe you me, there's good reason why they delayed the patch.  As many things as they fixed and added, there's also stuff that needs to be tweaked and tuned.
<br />

<br />
Training's going to be a pleasant surprise for everyone on Live; it's basically a free Adept II spell you get every 10 levels, some with nice extra benefits.  For example, at level 10, you can choose between a specialized Gift of the Magi, a specialized Magi's Shielding that also acts as a pet buff for Summoners, a specialized Lightning Burst with extra Stun effect, and a specialized Static Pulse.  At level 20, an Enchanter should get the chance to choose a specialized version of one of their 10-19 spells.  At level 30, a Coercer or Illusionist can choose to specialize one of their 20-29 spells, and so on.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
